1.9.3	Some RAID configurations require almost identical drives ; others permit drives of different sizes , but then they operate at the size of the smallest .	St
1.9.4	The general recommendation for multi-drive systems is to put the OS , program files , transient data and perhaps some relatively unimportant files on the C drive .	St
1.9.5	As these items do not change much and/or are not so important , this drive does not need to be backed up very frequently just when there is a major change .	St
1.9.6	Important data in newly generated or modified files needs to be backed up much more frequently ; all this should be stored on drive ( s ) separate from the C drive so that backups are faster and simpler .	St
